3. Market demand: The demand for the product or service being offered should also be considered. If there is high demand, then a marketing campaign may be more effective. If there are quality issues with the product, then improving product quality may be more important.
4. Competition: The level of competition in the market should also be considered. If there is a lot of competition, then a marketing campaign may be necessary to stand out. If the competition is low, then improving product quality may be more important.
