To make this code work with arrays of any data type, you can use generics in C#. Here's how you can modify the code:
```
public static T SumOfOddNumbers<T>(T[] arr)
{
    dynamic sum = default(T);
    for (int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
    {
        if (Convert.ToInt32(arr[i]) % 2 != 0)
        {
            sum += arr[i];
        }
    }
    return sum;
}
```
