Here's how we can implement this algorithm in C++:
1. Declare an integer array called "numList" and initialize it with the given list of integers.
2. Declare an integer variable called "sum" and initialize it to 0. This variable will be used to store the sum of all even numbers in the list.
3. Use a "for" loop to iterate through each element in the "numList" array. The loop should start at the first element (i.e., index 0) and continue until the last element in the array.
4. Inside the loop, use an "if" statement to check if the current element is even or odd. To check if an integer is even, we can use the modulo (%) operator. If the remainder of the current element divided by 2 is 0, then the current element is even. Otherwise, it's odd.
5. If the current element is even, add it to the "sum" variable.
6. After the loop has finished iterating through all the elements in the array, print out the value of the "sum" variable to the console, along with a message that describes what the value represents.
