Certainly! Here's a sample code for implementing a binary search algorithm in MATLAB:
```
function index = binarySearch(array, target)
    left = 1;
    right = length(array);
    while left <= right
        mid = floor((left + right) / 2);
        if array(mid) == target
            index = mid;
            return
        elseif array(mid) < target
            left = mid + 1;
        else
            right = mid - 1;
        end
    end
    index = -1;
end
```
In this code, `array` is the sorted array in which we want to search for `target`. The function `binarySearch` returns the index of the target element in the array if it is found, or -1 if it is not found.
The time complexity of binary search is O(log n), where n is the length of the array. This is because the algorithm repeatedly divides the search interval in half until the target element is found or the interval is empty. The space complexity is O(1), as the algorithm only requires a constant amount of extra space to store the variables `left`, `right`, `mid`, and `index`.
